00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:07,050
So what is Direct Connect?

80
00:03:07,050 --> 00:03:09,030
Well, it is a physical connection

81
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:12,837
between your infrastructure
and the AWS infrastructure.

82
00:03:12,837 --> 00:03:14,400
And I say physical connection

83
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,800
because it does involve cross-connects,

84
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,410
connecting pieces of
fiber between equipment

85
00:03:19,410 --> 00:03:22,110
to enable traffic to flow
from your infrastructure

86
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:25,443
into the AWS backbone
and into our regions.

87
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:29,790
Originally, it supported
a couple of connections,

88
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:34,290
perhaps in a location to
one region, perhaps one VPC,

89
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,360
but Direct Connect has
evolved a lot over the years

90
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,920
that I've been talking about it.

91
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,990
So Direct Connect now
supports connectivity

92
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:42,690
to multiple regions using
Direct Connect gateway,

93
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:45,330
and of course, multiple VPCs as a result.

94
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:47,520
And it also supports now
connecting into things

95
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:50,280
like Cloud WAN, transit
gateways, et cetera.

96
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,380
So Direct Connect has evolved over time,

97
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:53,730
as you would expect.

98
00:03:53,730 --> 00:03:55,500
But we're gonna go right
back to the beginning

99
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:59,010
in terms of establishing
these connections.

100
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:00,693
So that physical connectivity.

101
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:04,050
When you're establishing your first

102
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:05,280
Direct Connect with AWS,

103
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,410
one of the first
decisions you need to make

104
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:09,480
is where are you going to do it?

105
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,350
So as I like to say,

106
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:12,980
it's a location, location,
location discussion.

107
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,960
You need to go look on our website

108
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,860
and look at the different locations

109
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:18,870
that we have around the
world for Direct Connect.

110
00:04:18,870 --> 00:04:20,680
These are locations where
we have infrastructure

111
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:23,640
and we can provide ports
for you to connect to.

112
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,680
When you look at that
table on our website,

113
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,570
we list out the locations,

114
00:04:27,570 --> 00:04:30,060
we list out what is called
the associated region,

115
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:31,380
and the set of features available

116
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:33,330
at that particular location.

117
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:36,150
So if you wanted a particular
amount of bandwidth,

118
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:39,060
you can look down that
table and recognize,

119
00:04:39,060 --> 00:04:40,650
hey, this particular location,

120
00:04:40,650 --> 00:04:42,660
it supports the bandwidth that I need.

121
00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:47,130
And we support one gig, 10 gig,
100 gig, and 400 gig ports.

122
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:50,220
Not all locations have all of
those different bandwidths,

123
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:52,820
so check the list for which
one makes sense for you.

124
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,410
You're also gonna be
making a decision there

125
00:04:55,410 --> 00:04:57,270
based on where your infrastructure is.

126
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:59,850
And it might be that you have
your network infrastructure

127
00:04:59,850 --> 00:05:01,410
already in one of those locations,

128
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:03,990
which makes the choice really quite easy.

129
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:05,070
If, however, you're connecting

130
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:08,280
to some on-premises infrastructure
or another data center,

131
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,230
then you'd be choosing the
Direct Connect locations

132
00:05:10,230 --> 00:05:12,840
that are closer physically
to that data center,

133
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:15,060
because you're gonna have
to order the connectivity

134
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:18,033
from our Direct Connect
location to your infrastructure.

135
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:22,200
Now, creating a connection
is really quite simple.

136
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:25,020
Give it a name, choose the
location from that list.

137
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:26,430
There is an option at the bottom there

138
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:29,400
which says you would like
a MACSEC-enabled port.

139
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,890
And I'm gonna talk about that
a little bit more later on,

140
00:05:31,890 --> 00:05:33,760
but that's also listed in that table,

141
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:37,080
which locations support MACSEC.

142
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,393
So if you plan to use MACSEC,

143
00:05:38,393 --> 00:05:40,320
this is the time you make that decision.

144
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,210
It's not something you change later on.

145
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:44,370
If you would like a port
that is capable of MACSEC,

146
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:47,520
so encryption, choose it when you order

147
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,830
the connection at the beginning.

148
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:51,840
You're gonna notice
throughout the slides here

149
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:54,720
that we have these boxes
down in the bottom corner.

150
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,400
These are just to call
out some of the quotas

151
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,470
that we have around Direct Connect.

152
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:01,620
Many of these you can just
request an increase for.

153
00:06:01,620 --> 00:06:05,070
But in this example, it's 10 connections

154
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,380
per location per region.

155
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:07,860
That's your starting point

156
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,903
for ordering Direct Connect connections.

157
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,870
Okay, so we've ordered our connection.

158
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,640
We've clicked through on the console.

